                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18181028-135-victim940 t18181028-135-viclabel770"></join>, and lives in <placeName id="t18181028-135-crimeloc771">Church-lane, Chelsea</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18181028-135-crimeloc771" type="placeName" value="Church-lane, Chelsea"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18181028-135-crimeloc771" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18181028-135-off768 t18181028-135-crimeloc771"></join>. On the 5th of October I was working in the parlour, the prisoner, tried the door twice that evening, the third time he managed to open it without the bell ringing-the alarm was given - I saw him in the shop. He had pulled out two tills, which contained a quantity of halfpence, and silver. I ran to the door, and shut him in-my neighbours came to my assistance - He dropped the money on the floor - He had taken the silver, and left the halfpence - He had his shoes off.</p>
               <p>JOSEPH ADDY. I was sitting in the parlour about nine o'clock, and heard the prisoner in the shop-he was taken and he said his companions held the bell, while he opened the door-the floor was covered with silver, which he had thrown down.</p>
